			    STPJS 202</div>
  <p class="cont">out iniquity;<span class="footRef">1</span> said they must be extremely careful in all their examinations, or the consequences
  would be serious.</p>
  <p class="std">All difficulties which might and would cross our way must be surmounted. Though the soul be
  tried, the heart faint,<span class="footRef">2</span> and the hands hang down,<span class="footRef">3</span> we must not retrace out steps; there must be
  decision of character, aside from sympathy. When instructed, we must obey that voice,<span class="footRef">4</span> observe the
  laws<span class="footRef">5</span> of the Kingdom of God,<span class="footRef">6</span> that the blessings of heaven may rest down upon us.<span class="footRef">7</span> All must act
  in concert,<span class="footRef">8</span> or nothing can be done, and should move according to the ancient Priesthood; hence the
  Saints should be a select people,<span class="footRef">9</span> separate<span class="footRef">10</span> from all the evils of the world&mdash;choice, virtuous, and
  holy. The Lord was going to make of the Church of Jesus Christ a kingdom of Priests,<span class="footRef">11</span> a holy
  people,<span class="footRef">12</span> a chosen generation,<span class="footRef">13</span> as in Enoch&rsquo;s day,<span class="footRef">14</span> having all the gifts as illustrated to the Church
  in Paul&rsquo;s epistles and teachings to the churches in his day<span class="footRef">15</span>&mdash;that it is the privilege of each member
  to live long and enjoy health. He then blessed the Saints.<span class="footRef">16</span> (March 30, 1842.) DHC 4:570.</p>
  <div class="topic">&ldquo;Try the Spirits&rdquo;<span class="footRef">17</span></div>
  <div class="topic centerEmphasis">The Prophet&rsquo;s Editorial in the Times and Seasons</div>
  <p class="std">Recent occurrences that have transpired amongst us render it an imperative duty<span class="footRef">18</span> devolving
  upon me to say something in relation to the spirits by which men are actuated.</p>
  <p class="std">It is evident from the Apostles&rsquo; writings, that many false spirits existed in their day, and had
  &ldquo;gone forth into the world,&rdquo;<span class="footRef">19</span> and that it needed intelligence which God alone could impart to detect
  false spirits,<span class="footRef">20</span> and to prove what spirits were of God.<span class="footRef">21</span> The world in general have been grossly
  ignorant in regard to this one thing, and why should they be otherwise&mdash;for &ldquo;the things of God
  knoweth no man, but the Spirit of God.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">22</span></p>
  <p class="std">The Egyptians were not able to discover the difference between the miracles of Moses and those
  of the magicians until they came to be tested together;<span class="footRef">23</span> and if Moses had not appeared in their
  midst, they would unquestionably have thought that the miracles of the magicians were performed
  through the mighty power of God,<span class="footRef">24</span> for they were great miracles that were performed by them&mdash;a
  supernatural agency was developed, and great power manifested.</p>
  <p class="wideEllipse">* * *</p>

